Hi and thank you first for this Django-React integration solution.  

I would like to suggest adding to the "Template" section in the documentation, an explicit clarification that the bundle name to render in `{% render_bundle 'name' 'js' %}` is referring to the webpack entry name in the webpack configuration file and not some bundle file name prefix. 

For the following webpack entry configuration:
```javascript
module.exports = {
    entry: {
        index: ['whatwg-fetch', './src/index.js']
    },
    output: {
        path: path.resolve('dist'),
        filename: '[name].bundle.js'
    },...
```
I got he following webpack-stats:
```javascript
{"status":"done","chunks":{"index":[{"name":"index.bundle.js","path":"/[path]/ui/dist/index.bundle.js"}]}}
```
And got a  WebpackBundleLookupError because I was using `{% render_bundle 'index.bundle' 'js' %}` in my template. The error itself did not expose any explicit lookup logic problem stemming from the parameters: 

```javascript
assets :	{'chunks': {'index': [{'name': 'index.bundle.js',
                       'path': '[path]/ui/dist/index.bundle.js'},
                      ]},'status': 'done'}
bundle_name : 'index.bundle'
```

So I needed to look into the source code, using some old school debugging, to realize that what is referred to as "bundle_name" actually refers to the webpack configuration entry name ("index").

It might be obvious to most people but it wasn't for me, and i just wanted to post this issue and its resolution in case someone else could benefit from it.

@owais great work on this loader. In my use case, I like to build and post-process my production bundles locally and build them into the django project's static folder. These get deployed as part of `collectstatic`, and benefit from the staticfiles [hashing mixin](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.10/ref/contrib/staticfiles/#manifeststaticfilesstorage) which works great.

To keep my setup, I was wondering if there was a case for having the loader fallback to the standard static file loader when in production? 

